The paper deals with graph realization problems, which are typically studied in the sub-fields of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS). The problem of realizing a given degree sequence is a classic problem in graph theory and is often studied in the context of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper specifically deals with directed acyclic graphs, which is a topic studied in computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the paper also discusses fixed-parameter tractability, which is a topic studied in parameterized complexity theory (cs.GT).
